        The TEXT global attribute values from the CDF.

      • XYZ_PATTERN

        private static final java.util.regex.Pattern XYZ_PATTERN
        Regular expression pattern to identify CDF variables containing X, Y, and Z coordinate values. The cature group contains the coordinate system identifier.

      • COMPONENT_PATTERN

        private static final java.util.regex.Pattern COMPONENT_PATTERN
        Regular expression pattern to identify CDF variables containing component (X, Y, Z, lat, lon, or local-time) values. The first capture group contains the coordinate system identifer. The second capture group contains the component identifer.

      • B_TRACE_PATTERN

        private static final java.util.regex.Pattern B_TRACE_PATTERN
        Regular expression pattern to identify CDF variables containing B Trace values (North/South, GEO/GM, lat/lon/arc-length). The first capture group contains the North/South hemisphere value. The second capture group contains the coordinate system identifier. The third capture group contains the component identifier.

      • B_TRACE_STOP_ALTITUDE_PATTERN

        private static final java.util.regex.Pattern B_TRACE_STOP_ALTITUDE_PATTERN
        Regular expression pattern to capture the B Trace stop altitude value contained in the TEXT global attribute entries. The first capture group contains the stop altitude value.

      • UTC_TIME_ZONE

        private static final java.util.SimpleTimeZone UTC_TIME_ZONE
        A UTC TimeZone.

        private static final java.util.logging.Logger LOGGER
